data.oai_dc:dc: CT scan data of wild double-crested cormorant, Phalacrocorax auritus OUVC 10644

This zip file contains DICOM images from an x-ray microcomputed tomography (µCT) scan of an injected Phalacrocorax auritus (OUVC 10644). The veins were injected with a latex and barium solution and scanned on a GE eXplore Locus in vivo Small Animal MicroCT scanner (90µm slice thickness at 80kV and 450 µA) at the Ohio University µCT Scanning Facility.
